item.name: Alarms - Number of Present Alarms
item.description: The present number of active alarm conditions.

item.name: UPS User Identity
item.description: A user-supplied ID for the UPS.

item.name: UPS Serial Number
item.description: Serial number for the UPS.

item.name: UPS Software Checksum
item.description: A checksum for the UPS software.

item.name: Input - Number of Voltages
item.description: The number of input voltages. Phase to phase or phase to neutral. This variable indicates the number of rows in the input table.

item.name: Device Location
item.description: The device location string.

item.name: Outlet - Number of Outlets
item.description: The number of available Outlets in this device.

item.name: Output - Number of Voltages
item.description: The number of output circuits. This variable indicates the number of rows in the output circuit table.

item.name: UPS Selected Device ID
item.description: The device ID selected to be used for retrieving data for this mib. As the snmp web card has only one device, this is read only for it

item.name: SNMPWEBCARD Serial Number
item.description: Serial number for the SNMPWEBCARD.

item.name: Config - High Voltage Transfer Point
item.description: The maximum line voltage allowed before the UPS system transfers to battery backup.

item.name: Config - Input Voltage
item.description: The magnitude of the nominal input voltage. On those systems which support read-write access to this object, if there is an attempt to set this variable to a value that is not supported, the request must be rejected and the agent shall respond with an appropriate error message, i.e., badValue for SNMPv1, or inconsistentValue for SNMPv2.

item.name: Config - Low Voltage Transfer Point
item.description: The minimum input line voltage allowed before the UPS system transfers to battery backup.

item.name: Agent Software Version
item.description: The UPS agent software version. This variable may or may not have the same value as upsIdentUPSSoftwareVersion in some implementations.

item.name: Attached Devices
item.description: A string identifying the devices attached to the output(s) of the UPS. This object should be set by the administrator.

item.name: Manufacturer Identification
item.description: The name of the UPS manufacturer.

item.name: Model Identification
item.description: The UPS Model designation.

item.name: Device Name
item.description: A string identifying the UPS. This object should be set by the administrator.

item.name: UPS Software Version
item.description: The UPS firmware/software version(s). This variable may or may not have the same value as upsIdentAgentSoftwareVersion in some implementations.

item.name: Output - Number of Lines
item.description: The number of output lines utilized in this device. This variable indicates the number of rows in the output table.

item.name: Output - Source
item.description: The present source of output power. The enumeration none(2) indicates that there is no source of output power (and therefore no output power), for example, the system has opened the output breaker.

item_prototype.name: Input - Type of Input $1
item_prototype.description: Whether voltage measured is phase to phase or phase to neutral.

item_prototype.name: Input - Voltage of Input $1
item_prototype.description: The magnitude of the present input voltage. A value of 6553 indicates Unknown.

item_prototype.name: Outlet - Ndx group of outlet $1
item_prototype.description: tlUpsOutletGroupIndex of corresponding outlet group, or 0 if ungrouped.

item_prototype.name: Outlet - Name of outlet $1
item_prototype.description: A string identifying the devices attached to the output(s) of the device.

item_prototype.name: Outlet - Ramp action of outlet $1
item_prototype.description: The ramp action to take on the Outlet.

item_prototype.name: Outlet - Ramp data type of outlet $1
item_prototype.description: The type of data associated with ramp action.

item_prototype.name: Outlet - Ramp data of outlet $1
item_prototype.description: The data value associated with type of ramp data.

item_prototype.name: Outlet - Shed action of outlet $1
item_prototype.description: The shed action to take on the Outlet.

item_prototype.name: Outlet - Shed action data type of outlet $1
item_prototype.description: The type of data associated with shed action.

item_prototype.name: Outlet - Shed data of outlet $1
item_prototype.description: The data value associated with type of shed data.

item_prototype.name: Outlet - State of outlet $1
item_prototype.description: The current state of the Outlet.

item_prototype.name: Outlet - Type of outlet $1
item_prototype.description: This is a bit field that indicates the type of this Outlet. When 0, the outlet is not controllable and has none of the other features indicated in the bit map. When non-zero, the features present for this outlet can be interpreted with the definition.
